The operation $\bigtriangledown\times$ or \lq\lq curl\rq\rq~in (\ref{Faraday_eqn2}) and (\ref{Ampere_eqn2}) can be easily interpreted using this Yee-cell. For example, the $H_x$ component located at point (i,j+1/2,k+1/2) is surrounded by four circulating $\overrightarrow E$ components (two $E_y$ components and two $E_z$ components), exactly matching to the (\ref{FE_3a}), which states that the $H_x$ component increases directly in response to a curl of $\overrightarrow E$ components in x direction with a constant $\mu$. The constant $\mu$ specifies the magnetic permeability of the material at the location of this unit cell. Similarly, the $\overrightarrow E$ components increase directly in response to the curl of $\overrightarrow H$ components too, with a constant proportional to the electrical permittivity $\varepsilon$ of the material at the current location. Maxwell\rq s equations in rectangular coordinates, (\ref{FE_3a}) to (\ref{AE_3c}), can also be illustrated by Yee\rq s cell clearly.

As illustrated in Fig.~\ref{Fig:2d_yee_cell}, $\overrightarrow E$ and $\overrightarrow H$ components are interlaced not only in space but also in time. All $\overrightarrow E$ components are updated at $N\bigtriangleup t$ and all $\overrightarrow H$ components are updated at $(N+1/2)\bigtriangleup t$. In more detail, the $\overrightarrow E$ components in the N-th time step are updated and stored in memory using previously stored $\overrightarrow H$ data, and then the $\overrightarrow H$ components in the $(N + \frac{1}{2})$-th time step are updated and stored in memory also using the $\overrightarrow E$ data which are just calculated. This calculation can be iterated through time steps so the electromagnetic field values can be updated at any time interval. In this thesis, we represent an electric component $E_z$ at the discretized three-dimensional coordination $(i\bigtriangleup x, j\bigtriangleup y, (k+1/2)\bigtriangleup z)$ as $E_z(i,j,k+1/2)$, and when the current time is in the discretized n-th time step, we denote the same component as $E_z^n(i,j,k+1/2)$. The magnetic components are placed on a half time step; so the superscripts are half indicated as $H_x^{n+1/2}(i,j+1/2,k+1/2)$.

